      "title": "Update the brand's theme",
      "description": "## Update the brand's theme\n\nNext, we will update Okta Ice's theme by using the [Replace a theme](https://developer.okta.com/docs/api/openapi/okta-management/management/tag/Themes/#tag/Themes/operation/replaceBrandTheme) endpoint. This uses the `PUT` method, so it's a full replacement.\n\n1. **Click on the command** below to run the curl command from the API documentation. This will will Okta Ice's theme with a configuration that matches the default Okta theme.\n>> curl -i -X PUT \"$BASE_OKTA_URL/api/v1/brands/$BRAND_ID/themes/$THEME_ID\" -H \"Authorization: SSWS $OKTA_API_TOKEN\" -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{ \"primaryColorHex\": \"#1662dd\", \"primaryColorContrastHex\": \"#000000\", \"secondaryColorHex\": \"#ebebed\", \"secondaryColorContrastHex\": \"#000000\", \"signInPageTouchPointVariant\": \"OKTA_DEFAULT\", \"endUserDashboardTouchPointVariant\": \"OKTA_DEFAULT\", \"errorPageTouchPointVariant\": \"OKTA_DEFAULT\", \"emailTemplateTouchPointVariant\": \"OKTA_DEFAULT\", \"loadingPageTouchPointVariant\": \"OKTA_DEFAULT\"}'\n2. From the Okta Admin Console, go to **Customizations** > **Brands** and select **Okta Ice**.\n> Notice that the Sign-in page preview has reverted back to the Okta defaults. You can use the dropdown menu to preview the other pages to verify these changes were applied uniformly.\n2. Let's switch back to our custom Okta Ice theme. **Click on the command** below to run the curl command:\n>> curl -i -X PUT \"$BASE_OKTA_URL/api/v1/brands/$BRAND_ID/themes/$THEME_ID\" -H \"Authorization: SSWS $OKTA_API_TOKEN\" -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{ \"primaryColorHex\": \"#2d75bb\", \"primaryColorContrastHex\": \"#000000\", \"secondaryColorHex\": \"#c7e5f5\", \"secondaryColorContrastHex\": \"#000000\", \"signInPageTouchPointVariant\": \"BACKGROUND_IMAGE\", \"endUserDashboardTouchPointVariant\": \"FULL_THEME\", \"errorPageTouchPointVariant\": \"BACKGROUND_IMAGE\", \"emailTemplateTouchPointVariant\": \"FULL_THEME\", \"loadingPageTouchPointVariant\": \"NONE\" }'"
